# Voice Chat UI

- Keep voice input client-side with the Web Speech API unless a server route is introduced.
- Route all chat text through `POST /api/chat`; do not call providers directly from the client.
- Track `isListening`/`isSpeaking` to prevent overlapping audio and UI actions.
- Provide graceful fallback when SpeechRecognition isn't supported.

**TTS (spoken responses):** Implemented in `AIChat.tsx` and `ChatWidget.tsx` using the **browser Web Speech API** (`window.speechSynthesis` + `SpeechSynthesisUtterance`). No `utterance.voice`, `utterance.lang`, `utterance.rate`, or `utterance.pitch` are set — the **browser/OS default voice** is used. No third-party TTS or custom AI voice is used. See `docs/VOICE_TTS_CONFIGURATION.md` for full trace.

```tsx
const SpeechRecognition =
  (window as any).SpeechRecognition || (window as any).webkitSpeechRecognition;
if (!SpeechRecognition) return;
```
